===Etymology===
{{etyl|frm}} {{term|escroue||nut, socket|lang=frm}} (Modern French ''[[écrou]]''), from {{etyl|la}} {{term|scrofa||sow|lang=la}}, referring to the screw-like tip of a boar's penis.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[simple machine]], a [[helical]] inclined plane.
# A (usually) metal fastener consisting of a [[shank]] partially or completely [[threaded]] [[shank]], sometimes with a threaded point, and a [[head]] used to both hold the top material and to drive the screw either directly into a soft material or into a prepared hole.
# {{nautical}} A ship's [[propeller]].
# An [[Archimedes screw]].
# {{slang}} A prison officer.
# {{vulgar}} [[sexual intercourse|Sexual intercourse]]; the act of [[screwing]].
#: ''have a good '''screw'''''
# {{slang}} Salary, wages.
#* '''1888''', [[w:Rudyard Kipling|Rudyard Kipling]], [[s:In the Pride of His Youth|"In the Pride of His Youth"]]
#*: A certain amount of "'''screw'''" is as necessary for a man as for a billiard-ball.
# {{billiards}} [[backspin|Backspin]].

